Additional genes used for annotation: This cluster prominently expresses flp-10, flp-20, ceh-31, nlp-37 and srw-35 which are all markers of the PVR neurons (CeNGEN).

This cluster expresses mls-1 and C53B7.2 which are both vulval muscle markers (CeNGEN). Additionally, this cluster does not prominently express egl-15 and nkb-1 which are vm1 markers, while it prominently expresses lin-12 which is a vm2 marker.

This cluster is the only germ cluster to prominently express fog-3. This gene is  highly expressed in the pachytene region in both males and hermaphrodites. However, in hermaphrodites, fog-3 expression disappears after the late L4 stage when worms switch from spermatogenesis to oogenesis. This cluster prominently expresses  zipt-7.1, cdc-48.1, ubxn-2, him-3, vbh-1 and set-17 which are all gene markers for spermatocytes.
Notes: At the young adult stage most of the sperm in the hermaphrodite is mature sperm (PMID: 24718317). This cluster of spermatocytes may be result of imperfect synchrony or may be coming from the small population of male worms.

Additional genes used for annotation: This cluster prominently expresses cutl-8 and mam-5 which are gene markers for the cephalic and inner labial sockets (Packer et al.).

Notes: After subclustering we could identify a subpopulation of PHC neurons (CeNGEN markers).

Additional genes used for annotation: This cluster does not prominently express gene markers for the distal-most spermatheca cells: apx-1 and let-502. Additionally expresses mel-11, a marker for the spermatheca bag cells. This cluster also expresses ajm-1 and par-3 which are gene markers for the distal portion of the spermatheca bag as well as ipp-5 and gem-4 which are also markers of the distal spermatheca. When the spermatheca clusters were subclustered this cluster merged with the spermatheca neck cluster.

This cluster also prominently expresses kcc-3, hlh-17 and pros-1 which are cephalic sheath markers (Packer et al.). The cephalic sheath cells have already been identified however (cluster 39 which expresses these markers more prominently in addition to nhr-57 a cephalic cells gene markers not expressed in this cluster).
